FBIS3-13166 "drnes047_r_94002" FBIS-NES-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 SOUTH ASIA India Efforts of PRC, Iran Noted BK0903161894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 GMT 9 Mar 94 BK0903161894 Delhi All India Radio Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] China and Iran have asked Islamabad to defer voting on the human rights resolution on Kashmir in Geneva. This was announced by the Pakistan foreign minister, Sardar Asif Ahmad Ali, at Islamabad a short while ago. He told a press conference that consequently Pakistan has authorized China and Iran to decide the best course they feel is available for it. Earlier, Beijing and Tehran approached Islamabad to postpone for three hours the voting on the resolution this evening so that further consultation could be held on certain proposals made by them. These options included either withdrawal of the resolution or its indefinite deferment. PTI, quoting observers in Islamabad, says Pakistan can agree to withdraw the resolution.
